RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 74. Allowance Purse 31600. FOR REGISTERED PA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A PA-RESTRICTED RACE(S) OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 15 Allo wed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since April 15 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOXY JUNIOR stalked the pace from the inside, checked hard when the pacesetter went bad on the turn, then got back into stride and came four wide into the lane, closed well to get up in time, driving. SHUTUP AND HANG ON was well rated early, made a three wide bid on the turn to duel for command by the quarter pole, gained a short lead leaving the furlong marker and was clear by the sixteenth marker but was caught late to just miss. CHARM ALARM stalked the early pace and made a two wide bid on the turn and dueled for command by the quarter pole on the inside, then faded the final furlong and bested the rest. SPECTACULLARI was reserved early, came five wide into the lane and had no rally. PHANCY PHILLY was four wide into the first turn, tracked the early pace from the outside and tired. GREAT BARONESS set the pace on the inside and went bad on the turn and was pulled up, vanned off.

ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace inside, went bad turn, pulled up, vanned off

ENTRY.NAME: Shutup and Hang On
ENTRY.COMMENT: well rated, bid 3 wide, edged clear 1/16, caught

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, checked 5/16, came 4 wide, rallied, up late

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace 2 wide, bid 2 wide, dueled inside 1/4, faded

ENTRY.COMMENT: 4 wide first turn, tracked 4 wide, tired

ENTRY.OWNER: McClay Thomas G Sweigart Dennis and Cullari Salvatore
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved early, came 5 wide upper stretch, no rally,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 2 1 1/16M Turf CR: 89. Claiming Purse 19900. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since April 15 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) Preference to horses with the most starts at Penn National since May 31st 2022. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BORGOBYTHESEA was away alertly to set the pace on the inside while clear, well handled and shook clear leaving the turn, then maintained a safe margin to the wire to prove best, driving. DYNAMITE KARMA stalked the winner two wide, made a bid on the turn but was turned back, then ran on willingly to the wire but could to get to the winner, second best. CRAZY KATER was reserved early and saved ground, then finished well on the inside to best the rest. COLONEL MOORHEAD tracked the pace on the inside and came three wide into the lane and weakened. CASTAGNO was settled early two to three wide, then was two wide on the turn and swung out five wide leaving the turn and had no rally. PURPLE SHIRT was settled early towards the inside, made a three wide middle move but tired. SKILLFUL was off slowly, trailed early, came wide into the lane and had no rally.

ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved inside, saved ground turn, finished well inside,

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside, middle move 3 wide, tired

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace inside, came 3 wide, weakened,

ENTRY.NAME: Castagno
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, 2 wide turn, came 5 wide, no rally,

ENTRY.NAME: Dynamite Karma
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace 2 wide, bid 2 wide turn, ran on, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Skillful
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slowly, trailed, came wide upper stretch, no rally,

ENTRY.NAME: Borgobythesea
ENTRY.COMMENT: away alertly, set pace inside, well handled, kept safe late

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ON THE SHORTLIST vied for the lead on the outside and made a two wide bid on the turn to dispose of JAYLEE leaving the turn, but then was confronted by PRIZE DEBATE by the furlong marker, but slowly edged away from that rival and kept SATISFIED safe late to prove best under mild crop urging. SATISFIED was settled two wide early, inside on the far turn, came two wide into the lane and then finished well on the inside. WIN FOR LAILA was allowed to settle on the inside and had no rally. DON DIVA was four wide into the first turn, stalked the pace three wide and tired.
